{
  "stem": "11964.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Today I'm going to tell you to a-- take you to an altogether different world.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I took them away to a southern plantation in Georgia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I was talking to them about Tara, and about Melanie, and about Scarlet and, and Brett Butler.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And their eyes would open, and they would dream about it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I remember one girl, especially, green-eyed girl who, who, who would-- I would have thought would have looked just like Scarlett.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I said, goodbye Scarlett.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And she would say, no, I'd rather be Melanie.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So we were dreaming together.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Our ghetto did not have a wall, but our ghetto was guarded.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in certain places, we had fences, fences that were, that were strategically placed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was-- most of it was an open ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In other words, without the wall in the ghetto, in the very beginning.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then, of course, the guards were there constantly.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, we knew that we couldn't leave the ghetto because the guards were there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were different guards at different times.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Most of the guards were not German.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Most of the guards were Ukrainian or Poles.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And somebody once mentioned that there were also some Lithuanians there, although I never saw a Lithuanian.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I did meet Ukrainians and Poles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And also, the Jewish militia was also forced into guarding the ghetto on the outside.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There was a whole administration in the ghetto, so-called Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And Judenrat was a, a board of, of Jews who were entrusted with some kind of an administrative leadership.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Unfortunately, that leadership had a double-- was a double-edged sword, because they had to execute all the proclamations by, by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the proclamations came fast and furious.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
